_Pa'al_: The shoresh קדש has a [[_pa'al_]] form, which follows [[forms|regular conjugations]] for the _pa'al_. קדש in the _pa'al_ can mean:
- to be or become pure
- to be or become sacred/holy/connected
- to be or become separated or designated for a special purpose

_Pi'el_: The shoresh קדש has a [[_pi'el_]] form, which follows [[forms|regular conjugations]] for the _pi'el_. קדש in the _pi'el_ can mean:
- to make something holy
- to create _kiddushin_, the first stage of marriage, with a woman
- saying _kiddush_ before a meal on Shabbos or Yuntif

_Hif'il_: The shoresh קדש has a [[_hif'il_]] form, which follows [[forms|regular conjugations]] for the _hif'il_. קדש in the _pa'al_ can mean:
- to be or become pure
- to be or become sacred/holy/connected
- to be or become separated or designated for a special purpose

_Hispa'el_: The shoresh קדש has a [[_hispa'el_]] form, which follows [[forms|regular conjugations]] for the _hispa'el_. קדש in the _pa'al_ can mean:
- to be or become pure
- to be or become sacred/holy/connected
- to be or become separated or designated for a special purpose

_Pu'al_ form: The shoresh קדש has a [[_pu'al_]] form, which follows [[forms|regular conjugations]] for the _pu'al_. קדש in the _pa'al_ can mean:
- to be or become pure
- to be or become sacred/holy/connected
- to be or become separated or designated for a special purpose

_Huf'al_: The shoresh קדש has a [[_huf'al_]] form, which follows [[forms|regular conjugations]] for the _huf'al. קדש in the _pa'al_ can mean:
- to be or become pure
- to be or become sacred/holy/connected
- to be or become separated or designated for a special purpose

Kiddushin: _Kiddushin_ is a stage of the marriage process. A man creates kiddushin with a woman, after which she is designated to him and needs to receive a divorce to remarry. After this stage, there is _nisyuin_, after which the marriage process is complete.
